Old Mutual CEO, Peter Moyo, has been refused entry to his office for the third time. The High Court ordered his temporary reinstatement after he was fired for an alleged conflict of interest. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Old Mutual CEO, Peter Moyo, has been refused entry to his office yet again. READ: Old Mutual given 10 days to explain their actions The High Court ordered his temporary reinstatement after he was fired for an alleged conflict of interest. Moyo said Old Mutual can't continue hiding behind their lawyers. READ: Peter Moyo back in court against Old Mutual Moyo was fired in June over an alleged conflict of interest. This is the third time Moyo has attempted to re-enter the Old Mutual offices after the High Court ordered his reinstatement.